cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.OS, cs.PL, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new library of datastructures for persistent memory. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of persistent memory in recoverable applications. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of persistent memory in the context of system reboots and power failures. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of functional programming techniques for space-reducing structural sharing. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the performance implications of unordered, overlapping flushes in Intel Optane PM hardware.
